SRC_11798	high	name_desc	src/mystic.c	539	19	Mystics are masters of bare-handed fighting, like Monks. Unlike Monks, though, they do not learn normal spells; instead, they gain mystical powers with experience, and these powers directly influence their martial arts. In this respect, Mystics are somewhat similar to Samurai; indeed, they even concentrate to boost their mana like the Samurai. Mystics eschew weapons of any kind, and require the lightest of armors in order to practice their martial arts. As with other martial artists, their attack speed depends on their level and Dexterity; their mana and fail rates, though, are influenced by Charisma. Mystics are in tune with the natural forces around them, and may even summon animals to their aid when necessary. It is whispered that mystics have discovered a way to kill an opponent with a single touch; but they do not share this knowledge with novices.		me.desc = "Mystics are masters of bare-handed fighting, like Monks. Unlike Monks, though, they "	
