SRC_19627	low	other	src/warlock.c	1535	3	An alliance with hounds is sneakily strong: hounds are fast, stealthy and nimble, and the warlock will gain these attributes as well, in addition to basic elemental resistances. They also gain decent melee, and the ability to channel the unpredictable powers of the aether. Of course, Hound Warlocks may also call on their kin for assistance, though this may not be enough against the more difficult foes of the world. Still, wouldn't it be fun to have some of those annoying hounds on your side for a change?		"An alliance with hounds is sneakily strong: hounds are fast, stealthy and nimble, "	
